SKILL|opencode|"Delegate coding to OpenCode CLI (features, PR review)."
STEP|1|Verify tool readiness:
STEP|2|For bounded tasks, use `opencode run '...'` (no pty needed).
STEP|3|For iterative tasks, start `opencode` with `background=true, pty=true`.
STEP|4|Monitor long tasks with `process(action="poll"\|"log")`.
STEP|5|If OpenCode asks for input, respond via `process(action="submit", ...)`.
STEP|6|Exit with `process(action="write", data="\x03")` or `process(action="kill")`.
STEP|7|Summarize file changes, test results, and next steps back to user.
PIT|Interactive `opencode` (TUI) sessions require `pty=true`. The `opencode run` command does NOT need pty.
PIT|`/exit` is NOT a valid command — it opens an agent selector. Use Ctrl+C to exit the TUI.
PIT|PATH mismatch can select the wrong OpenCode binary/model config.
PIT|If OpenCode appears stuck, inspect logs before killing:
PIT|Avoid sharing one working directory across parallel OpenCode sessions.
PIT|Enter may need to be pressed twice to submit in the TUI (once to finalize text, once to send).